text: Interstate 69 is a partially completed Interstate Highway in the United States. The main part of it goes from Indianapolis, Indiana north to Port Huron, Michigan at the Canada border. This part of the route is long. There are also parts of Interstate 69 in Mississippi and near Evansville, Indiana that are not currently connected to the other part but some are under construction. They will be connected when Interstate 69 is fully built from Indianapolis southwest to Texas. == References == 69
title: Interstate 69
